  "texts": [
    "The host integrates this output into the ongoing interaction, enabling more accurate and context-aware responses.",
    "By standardizing this communication pipeline, MCP decouples model behavior from tool implementation, supporting modular, extensible, and cross-platform agentic workflows.2) Google's A2A: Unlike the MCP, which focuses on connecting individual LLMs with external data sources and tools, Google's A2A protocol serves as a networking layer to facilitate seamless interoperability among heterogeneous AI agents.",
    "It facilitates direct communication and knowledge sharing for task collaboration.",
    "A2A incorporates enterprise-grade authentication and authorization mechanisms compliant with OpenAPI standards by default [9], such as OAuth 2.0 and OpenID Connect.A2A facilitates communication between a client agent and a remote agent [9], as shown in Fig. 10.",
    "The client agent formulates and transmits tasks, while the remote agent responds by executing the tasks or providing relevant information."
